<div class="mb-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-4">
  <div>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
      Tenants
      <span class="badge text-sky-600 ml-2" data-variant="outline">MULTI-TENANCY</span>
    </h1>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground">
      NodeDB server-side isolation: users are bound to a tenant at
      <code>CREATE USER … TENANT &lt;name&gt;</code>, and every connection
      authenticated as that user sees only the tenant's own collections.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="alert mt-4" role="alert">
  <i class="ti ti-info-circle"></i>
  <h2>How this demo works.</h2>
  <section>
    <p>
    There is no <code>SET TENANT</code> — tenancy binds per <em>user</em>, per
    <em>connection</em>. Provisioning runs
    <code>CREATE TENANT</code> + <code>CREATE USER t_&lt;name&gt; … TENANT &lt;name&gt;</code>
    over the app's normal superuser connection; the per-tenant playground then
    opens a short-lived <code>NodeDB::Connection</code> as that tenant user for
    each request. A production multi-tenant app would keep a connection pool per
    tenant (Rails <code>connects_to</code>) instead of reconnecting — this demo
    keeps the mechanics visible. Generated tenant passwords are stored in
    plaintext in the <code>tenant_registry</code> collection: demo-only,
    disposable data. <strong>Provision-only:</strong> there is no retire
    button — <code>DROP USER</code> currently leaves dangling catalog owner
    references that fail the daemon's boot integrity check on restart
    (upstream BUG-035), so tenants stay once created.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>

<%= form_with url: tenants_path, method: :post, local: true, class: "card mt-4" do |f| %>
  <section>
    <div class="grid gap-4 items-end md:grid-cols-4">
      <div role="group" class="field md:col-span-2">
        <%= f.label :name, "Tenant name" %>
        <%= f.text_field :name, class: "input", placeholder: "acme_corp",
              pattern: "[a-z][a-z0-9_]{2,29}" %>
        <p>3–30 chars: lowercase letter first, then a–z 0–9 _</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <%= f.submit "Provision tenant", class: "btn" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
<% end %>

<div class="card mt-4">
  <header>
    <h2>Provisioned tenants</h2>
    <div class="card-action text-muted-foreground text-sm"><%= @tenants.size %> tenants · counters via <code>SHOW TENANTS</code></div>
  </header>
  <section>
    <div class="table-container">
      <table class="table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Tenant</th>
            <th>Bound user</th>
            <th>Created</th>
            <th class="text-end">Total requests</th>
            <th class="text-end">Rejected</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <% @tenants.each do |t| %>
            <% c = @counters[t.id] %>
            <tr>
              <td><%= link_to t.id, tenant_path(t), class: "font-semibold" %></td>
              <td><code><%= t.username %></code></td>
              <td class="text-muted-foreground text-sm"><%= t.created_at %></td>
              <td class="text-end"><code><%= c ? c["total_requests"] : "?" %></code></td>
              <td class="text-end"><code><%= c ? c["rejected_requests"] : "?" %></code></td>
            </tr>
          <% end %>
          <% if @tenants.empty? %>
            <tr>
              <td colspan="5" class="text-muted-foreground text-center">
                No tenants yet — provision one above.
              </td>
            </tr>
          <% end %>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
